22:36.019 --> 22:37.842
And why aren't we treating him like he's here?

22:38.690 --> 22:42.476
Why isn't every time we come into the house, our hearts aren't filled with exceeding joy?

22:42.837 --> 22:50.088
Yeah, okay, it may not look like much, but we're in God's presence when we come together.

22:51.591 --> 22:53.594
And not just for Christmas, but every time.

22:54.395 --> 23:04.211
And yet we sometimes walk in with sadness and despair, not realizing that Jesus is here to meet our every need.

23:04.231 --> 23:06.194
We halfway,

23:06.274 --> 23:15.045
put aside our problems and our issues to lay down at his feet worship and to honor him for who he really is.

23:18.509 --> 23:22.253
I think the real problem is, for some, you stop looking for him.

23:24.676 --> 23:36.050
And I wanna encourage you, this first part of talking about what are you expecting for Christmas, I want you to start desiring in your heart to look for Jesus everywhere you go.

23:37.986 --> 23:42.851
Now some in the world would mock that saying, well, where you're looking for him, have you lost him?

23:43.171 --> 23:47.176
No, I'm talking about seeing the miracle of what he's done everywhere you go.

23:50.038 --> 23:55.104
Because if we're not gonna celebrate Jesus, to me, what's the point of having Christmas at all?

23:56.445 --> 24:05.074
If we're not going to look and find his goodness, look for his miracles, look for his grace in our lives, then we're missing the reason why he came in the first place.

24:07.842 --> 24:14.449
Jesus, we should be seeking after Him every day of our lives like those wise men.

24:17.853 --> 24:25.121
Every day wanting to know Him more, digging deeper, searching harder, because He is what we need to exist.

24:36.113 --> 24:37.234
I don't want to get to a point.

24:38.242 --> 24:42.947
where I stopped looking, where I give up.

24:46.271 --> 24:47.652
I can't imagine that horrible place.

24:50.395 --> 24:59.786
Can you imagine what would happen if the wise men had walked into Jerusalem heard that there was no king born to Herod and walked away?

25:02.869 --> 25:04.070
Because that's what happened originally.

25:06.353 --> 25:07.314
But they kept looking.

25:08.098 --> 25:11.543
because they needed to find him.

25:11.563 --> 25:13.766
And you and I need to keep looking till we find him, too.

25:16.830 --> 25:20.194
Thank you for watching today's service, but you really should visit in person.

